I don‚Äôt know how many of you know.. there is an app to check voter registration status and information. It is called Geaux Vote. (Louisiana only) it is an easy way to verify personal voter status to make sure it is active. It tells you how to reach your representatives (state and federal) locations of voting and how to request a mail in ballot. I have to follow up on the directions to follow up on provisional ballots, but it requires a trip to Baton Rouge. We have to let people know if they are told to fill out a provisional ballot after signing the registrar it isn‚Äôt normal. Provisional ballots are Only necessary If they cannot find your name in the book and/or something is wrong with the machines.
Also make sure to check your registration regularly! Texas purged a million voters from their rolls. We want to be sure that when we show up to the polls, we're squared away.

Hey Paula, I‚Äôm in New Orleans but my wife went to tech so love the area up there. The Harris-Walz campaign is focused on a swing state strategy so most official efforts and investment are geared towards GA, NC, AZ, PA, MI, WI, NV. One thing I learned during Gov Edwards‚Äô reelection campaign is that so much activity is driven at the grassroots/volunteer level which is why the campaign set us up with this platform here. I‚Äôve connected with students at Tulane and have been focused on encouraging voter registration via vote.org. The great thing about vote.org is that by going to that single site, you can get registered in any state. We can encourage students from the swing states listed above (along with Florida which has a competitive Senate race) to register in their home state. Ultimately, students have the choice to register where they are residing for school or in their home state. I think that could be a great first step for the college students.
I attended one of these Organize your Family and Friends trainings and found it very useful: https://events.democrats.org/event/597621/

Also, for anyone looking to do canvassing: while Georgia may be the closest true presidential swing state based on 2020 map, Florida has an extremely competitive U.S. Senate election that could be the tipping point for Senate majority. Pensacola has a field office and is organizing canvassing (door knocking and community mobilization), https://www.mobilize.us/2024flvictory/
More canvassing opportunities in Columbus, Georgia which is right across the Alabama, Georgia state line: Want to join me for this 2024 GA Victory event? https://mobilize.us/s/VTGNwJ

**Strict Fundraising Rules (it‚Äôs the law):**
We can only fundraise on behalf of: Democratic National Committee, Harris Victory Fund or Harris for President directly. Fundraising includes online stores like the Louisiana Party Store
When in doubt, ask @ moderator. You can repost mentioning the store or the items available as long as you remove the link.

**Strict Fundraising Rules (it‚Äôs the law):**
We can only fundraise on behalf of: Democratic National Committee, Harris Victory Fund or Harris for President directly. 
We can recruit for "non-official events" that are hosted by partner organizations or volunteers in ‚Å†non-official-events-only. We can recruit into anything that is listed on events.democrats.org or a state democratic party's mobilize.
Rule 3 Note > Relevance: Do not post links to petitions or other calls to action that haven‚Äôt been approved by Staff. This forum is not intended for debates. Additionally, do not attempt to raise funds or share fundraising links for any entity besides the Democratic National Committee. Using this server to raise funds for yourself, another candidate, or another organization violates campaign finance law and is strictly prohibited. Anyone who violates the rules is subject to removal or time out.
When in doubt, ask @Community Moderator.
